[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Clarifying resource paths**\n\nI need to properly set the resource path and add src/test/resources/mp-meta-config.properties with add-default-sources=true. It seems this will make every getConfig() use meta instead of default converters unless add-discovered-converters is true. Our getConfig with getValue(String, String.class) has a built-in converter that works, but I’m not sure about others. I should create a public class test file and assert that config source names include System properties. Also, I need to consider potential issues with classpath resource lookup and upstream jar configurations.\n\n**Examining system property behavior**\n\nSetting the system property makes findMetaConfig(fileName) call findFile and findClasspath(getResource(customname)). If the resource is missing, I can set the property to \"missing-mp-meta-config.properties,\" which would trigger a call to getResource even when null. This would lead to a fallback to default resources. However, it seems existing tests don't invoke getConfig. Instead, we could use ConfigProviderResolver.instance().getConfig, which would utilize defaults. I wonder if this could affect default sources. It's challenging to figure out what works best without assertions!\n\n**Analyzing resource handling**\n\nIf there's no meta resource, it will trigger getResource to read system properties. I need to assert that the default source reads the system prop appropriately. This setup could effectively cover getResource. In buildConfig, if meta=MpMetaConfig.metaConfig and no environment or system meta config is found, it will look for defaults, leading to getResource for YAML and properties. It seems that no resource is necessary for this. However, I wonder if setting the meta-config system property in the test might be beneficial, just in case the current directory has an mp-meta-config file.\n\n**Considering test class mapping**\n\nI’m thinking about the one-to-one mapping for the test class named MpMetaConfigTest. I need to be careful not to compile or run anything at this stage. It might be a good idea to inspect the dynamic report to ensure that it only reflects the class. My goal is clarity and accuracy as I’m trying to make sure everything aligns correctly!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_027a1594cf2c1d3d016a237166335c8195965aa7ffcb6c1750\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqI3F-SAYC-HDCz9j4y-n_hw3O1qPz8ETWqJvHsGtqKNcP0-7pBuGTqxDTWEBsAGqz3Hg-KTkIuZfcsdXfnYJ_6P4e9Sox6YfcgEhXnJbah9RVHivvSCOIIIEE4HQ8GwEq49ftOTxILAPjZClsVDY42pVqR_TvvjHznLOC8fFvsUN9lcbPXuFShqrq6c9EroMy2q4qRnRbBYs7N4WIiC9yZETGg9zK9uJieW63hYX27Hyf1yPuc6wcauug-iU2GGiK00nxyB6agP1-jCam5MwI4qM5-OaACcMeRwg01AOW8PfaeyY7-LdinA6XoZAArZFo2nDozIDZCijr1K5_OTO_FjMMA_SPhtNxPvADsu0FFwc9AROvEUMIg6f0YQol6dDtgQgCRSlvXHmbxNjblD3u6A23wcv16Oowy0DZm9188RK6c460XpsimsxDFsF7oXSgjk-1hgJI6sdu2ux1Bp6CTLH12YBJINzdo2ZlQZ1jRpO6QJ0jHpoHBGasE4Def9RkT2YhM46AmpFMbBbqMBxkGmREXMlV3YXjabQmwnURn9nDLuUBaIqw61pGoO9eOZTb7sXtjzu-eEKuaTwtpmyV3-MnS_EZ53IusoxexYgRrVIJKiULudeVPwCO84_ZiZ67COZPUIQ4WMiXhqsrmAwWIcGACBAJZzuqWtUcjCXW8PRynrIS-BTXF1YNW71yVmGx6d6hJy7oHqMxXUNtijku08wCyjokIMEDS-CfjOL5A13gobIe22nTqUBsvFd_PW_hLlxU7fr2rWtnWNJpTfhm7KXQ5gEqberyXaw4dp_JV605arYPLAGEoloGjlQb5b3I1D2DbJG9fMCLl0f1K1w1_R6Vyr1tyqXtFYrbzhN1Lk4OqhTcbscRxY-2bu3hWHvtf3xs9fl5yGg5aMbAd90-QmfSl9V7YyydUkrIwx4-m0s56TPtxwjijh-EIORGuw2UUPoxL9zyyook60H-XgZnXZiPgi_eGch7p7DR2pW-jUK_xblMdEsCOAcOsiEOsl1-TIloriKhLNFr2hDHHR1SEyjqdptblMwjwyIWwwHABGXihH3QD-8PyMgjuLSN7wpl_wHxb-MlthrR956CwTv9LYrm2jH1gBKkt7pnbUjkWwZVM-vQB7lBzCjlp40_t6b9R3xlMmVSexGUwbicAq9vqA17WVLbc-nl4CZKj-EWbcNUQywPIrguBN-j9PVJXMunyhVOoVDBdBJiHbcRmwsnvTjF_mn88qXHJ5KukJqL5cTibR6F52x9Ssd9bEMPvDCOct0wQMV4p4lUkbUV24RQXxlWIo7zOck5IPSVmknMFE81s4qpo5Nwm6qWCGidCA2UmsSfeOlWah-Sr7G_AtJ-CHBZYepBVQmDtKOAQKMm0qOECEdnuc4MaptZqwIm7F19YObYY8psMiiZDYVmXu7P_WYpiZm9TalQGSfc6bZcrxGqaMKiR18WSjx7UeAQ21x4UqOtAuUHLanG3